cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.CE 

This paper deals with incentivizing individuals in social networks to promote campaigns, which falls under the category of social influence and social networks (cs.SI) and computational social science (cs.SOC). The use of percolation theory and optimization algorithms also suggests a possible fit under mathematical aspects of computer science (cs.MA) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the focus on minimizing cost and resource constraints suggests a possible fit under computer engineering (cs.CE).
